obo:GO_0031594  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_1037  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: This publication demonstrates that in drosophila, liprin-a is involved in the assembly of presynaptic terminals at the NMJ.\n\n-dLiprin-a null have a reduced number of presynaptic terminals without affecting muscle innervation (figure 4, 5).\n\nThe morphology of the remaining boutons is affected. Boutons are smaller (figure 5) and have larger active zones (figure 8). The latter is in line with findings in C. elegans (Zhen and Jin 1999).\n\nIn line with a reduction in the number of boutons, mutants have reduced evoked EJP amplitude (Figure 9), demonstrating that the overal neurotransmitter release is reduced.\n\nIn line with defects in presynaptic assembly, Miller et.al. (2005) shows that dLiprin-a null have defects in trafficking of presynaptic vesicles.\n\ndLiprin-a has 47% homology with human liprin-a, with up to 95% homology in its SAM domains.. Experimental description: In this study, we report the identification of Drosophila Liprin-α (Dliprin-α) as a protein that interacts with the cytoplasmic domain of Drosophila Lar (Dlar). Expression analysis of the one Liprin-α family member in Drosophila reveals localization of Liprin-α to the neuromuscular synapse." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1037" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_7227" .

